  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ICT Security Engineer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Role Overview</strong></h3><p><br />We are seeking an experienced ICT Security Engineer to support cybersecurity governance, risk and compliance (GRC) and security assurance across end-user computing, on-premise infrastructure and cloud environments, aligned with Singapore Government IM8 requirements.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Develop and maintain cybersecurity standards, procedures and rulesets aligned to IM8 and best practices.</p></li><li><p>Conduct security risk assessments for system deviations, system changes and new project functionalities.</p></li><li><p>Perform security reviews and embed security-by-design principles into ICT solution design, including documenting security control requirements and secure configuration baselines aligned to enterprise architecture.</p></li><li><p>Conduct system hardening checks using CIS Benchmarks and IM8 standards, and ensure remediation of security gaps and audit findings.</p></li><li><p>Perform vulnerability assessment and manage VAPT outcomes, including risk rating and remediation recommendations.</p></li><li><p>Support security monitoring and incident triage (phishing, malware, endpoint alerts) and coordinate escalation where required.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate periodic security reviews and audit activities (AGO/GovTech/internal), including RFI management and evidence collection.</p></li><li><p>Support cloud and infrastructure security governance, including security patch monitoring and prioritisation using CVSS risk ratings.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Degree in Computer Science / IT / Cybersecurity or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 3 years relevant cybersecurity experience.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with tools such as Tenable/Nessus, Splunk, and cloud security platforms (AWS Security Hub / Microsoft Defender/Sentinel).</p></li><li><p>Security certifications (CISSP/CISM/CISA/GCIH/AWS/Azure Security) preferred.</p></li></ul>",
